&quot;I Wanna Lick It/Can I Speak To Mark With Electricity?&quot; features the 1975 Kiss hit &quot;Rock and Roll All Nite&quot; in its entirety. This is due to Gene Ween recording the album on old cassettes with music already on the tape. This effect is also heard on the Ween song &quot;&quot;, which near the end of the song Pink Floyd&#x27;s song &quot;Echoes&quot; kicks in. Other examples of this effect happening in Ween&#x27;s discography are on &quot;I Play It Off Legit&quot; and &quot;Flies On My Dick&quot;.

